cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NEURAL

The paper presents an algorithmic framework for learning multiple related tasks, which involves exploiting prior knowledge that relates the output spaces of these tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and natural language processing, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NEURAL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the learning framework and natural language processing tasks presented in the paper.
